1st immunogen - Name: Envelope glycoprotein precursor (Env polyprotein)

Reference - Authors: J M Ball; K E Rushlow; C J Issel; R C Montelaro
Reference - Title: Detailed mapping of the antigenicity of the surface unit glycoprotein of equine infectious anemia virus by using synthetic peptide strategies.
1st immunogen - Name: Equine infectious anemia virus (equine infectious anemia virus EIAV)
Immunization - Comments: Mice were injected subcutaneously and intraperitoneally with disrupted virus in Freund complete adjuvant. Mice were boosted on days 14 and 28 with the same antigen preparation and dose in Freund incomplete adjuvant. On day 88, mice received a final booster dose in phosphate buffer. Spleen cells were obtained 4 days after the last injection for fusion to myeloma cells.
Assay - Comments: The epitope was determined by testing overlapping peptides spanning residues 44-74.

1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 2 doses at day 0 and day 21

Reference - Authors: S Rosati; A Mannelli; T Merlo; N Ponti
Reference - Title: Characterization of the immunodominant cross-reacting epitope of visna maedi virus and caprine arthritis-encephalitis virus capsid antigen.
1st immunogen - Name: Caprine arthritis encephalitis virus (Caprine arthritis-encephalitis virus)
Immunization - Comments: Positive sera were from 10 different flocks in which caprine arthritis-encephalitis virus (CAEV) infection had been clinically and serologically diagnosed and were selected based on their reactivity against MVV recombinant p25.
Assay - Comments: Four different recombinant subunits of ovine lentivirus p25 were tested against sera from infected goats. The highest ELISA absorbances were obtained with a 29 amino acid subunit located in the N-terminal half of p25. Through the analysis of overlapping peptides spanning this region the authors identified a 17 amino acid sequence as being shared by all fragments. This peptide is therefore considered a potential immunodominant and cross-reactive epitope. The conserved domain between CAEV and MMV is LNEEA + RW-R-NPP---.

Reference - Authors: Giuseppe Bertoni; Christian Hertig; Marie-Luise Zahno; Hans-Rudolf Vogt; Sophie Dufour; Pablo Cordano; Ernst Peterhans; William P Cheevers; Pierre Sonigo; Gianfranco Pancino
Reference - Title: B-cell epitopes of the envelope glycoprotein of caprine arthritis-encephalitis virus and antibody response in infected goats.
Epitope - Source Organism: Caprine arthritis encephalitis virus strain Cork
Epitope - Comments: The sequence is derived from the one published by Saltarelli et al (1990), Virology 179, 347-364 [PMID:2171210].
1st immunogen - Name: Caprine arthritis encephalitis virus strain Cork (Caprine arthritis encephalitis virus (STRAIN CORK))
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Caprine arthritis encephalitis virus strain Cork
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 5 doses of 10^6 TCID50
Immunization - Comments: Animals were infected from birth by feeding colostrum containing the virus from day 1 to 5, as described in Knowles et al, J Virol. 1991 Nov;65(11):5744 [PMID 1656067], or given 1 dose of 10^7 TCID.
Assay - Comments: Sera from five experimentally infected goats were used to select clones from a library of fragments of env protein. The fragment 18-113 selected was subsequently shown to be recognized by its N-terminal region, the epitope region SU1-mature. Subsequently, sera from six additional goats was tested for recognition of the region 21-112, and reactivity was minor, and shown only as late seroconversion (1 to 3.5 years post infection).
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Caprine arthritis encephalitis virus strain Cork

Reference - Authors: J Richardson; A Moraillon; F Crespeau; S Baud; P Sonigo; G Pancino
Reference - Title: Delayed infection after immunization with a peptide from the transmembrane glycoprotein of the feline immunodeficiency virus.
1st immunogen - Name: RAISSWKQRNRWEWRPD
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 5 doses of 120 μg of FIV peptide (approximately 250 μg of KLH-coupled peptide)
Immunization - Comments: Four booster injections were administered subcutaneously in incomplete Freund´s adjuvant, at intervals of 2 to 3 weeks for the 1st, 2nd and 3rd, and 7 weeks for the 4th. A tyrosine residue was added at the N-terminus of the peptide for coupling to KLH.
Assay - Comments: Significant recognition of the immunizing peptide could be detected in all the immunized animals. One week after the last immunization, cats were challenged with the Wo isolate of FIV, and the response to other viral components (recombinant capsid protein, TM2 peptide) as a function of time after challenge revealed no differences between peptide-vaccinated and adjuvant control groups.

Reference - Authors: R Skraban; S Matthíasdóttir; S Torsteinsdóttir; G Agnarsdóttir; B Gudmundsson; G Georgsson; R H Meloen; O S Andrésson; K A Staskus; H Thormar; V Andrésdóttir
Reference - Title: Naturally occurring mutations within 39 amino acids in the envelope glycoprotein of maedi-visna virus alter the neutralization phenotype.
Epitope - Comments: This region differs in four substitutions and two deletions between the molecular clones LV1-1KS1 and KV1772kv72/67.
1st immunogen - Name: Visna/maedi virus EV1 KV1772 (Visna lentivirus (strain KV1772))
Immunization - Comments: The infecting virus is described as strain KV1772kv72/67. It is a molecular clone derived from strain KV1772.
Assay - Comments: The KV1772kv72/67 virus with the epitope region exchanged for the sequence of  LV1-1KS1 (recombinant virus VR1) is not neutralized by KV1772kv72/67 specific sera, implying there is no cross-reactive recognition of the epitope.

Reference - Authors: R Skraban; S Matthíasdóttir; S Torsteinsdóttir; G Agnarsdóttir; B Gudmundsson; G Georgsson; R H Meloen; O S Andrésson; K A Staskus; H Thormar; V Andrésdóttir
Reference - Title: Naturally occurring mutations within 39 amino acids in the envelope glycoprotein of maedi-visna virus alter the neutralization phenotype.
Epitope - Comments: This region differs in four substitutions and two deletions between the molecular clones LV1-1KS1 and KV1772kv72/67.
1st immunogen - Name: DLKCSLPHRNESNKWTCAARRKGSRRDSLYIAGRDFWGR
Immunization - Comments: The infecting virus is made of the KV1772kv72/67 virus where the epitope region was exchanged for the sequence of strain LV1-1KS1.
Assay - Comments: LV1-1KS1 was neutralized almost to the same extent as the infecting recombinant VR1, whereas KV1772kv72/67 was not neutralized, implying that the specific neutralization phenotype resides in the region transferred between the viruses in the recombinant immunogen.

Reference - Title: Naturally occurring mutations within 39 amino acids in the envelope glycoprotein of maedi-visna virus alter the neutralization phenotype.
Epitope - Comments: The epitope was deduced from analysis of overlapping peptides.
1st immunogen - Name: DLKCSLPHRNESNKWTCAARRKGSRRDSLYIAGRDFWGR
Immunization - Comments: The infecting virus is made of the KV1772kv72/67 virus where a 39-aa region containing the epitope was exchanged for the sequence of strain LV1-1KS1.

Reference - Authors: G Bertoni; M L Zahno; R Zanoni; H R Vogt; E Peterhans; G Ruff; W P Cheevers; P Sonigo; G Pancino
Reference - Title: Antibody reactivity to the immunodominant epitopes of the caprine arthritis-encephalitis virus gp38 transmembrane protein associates with the development of arthritis.
1st immunogen - Name: Caprine arthritis encephalitis virus (Caprine arthritis-encephalitis virus)
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 1 ml of 10E7 50% tissue culture infective doses/ml
Immunization - Comments: Goats were infected with 1 ml of supernatant (10E7 50% tissue culture infective doses/ml) of goat synovial membrane (GSM) cells transfected with the CAEV-CO molecular clone. A total of 0.5 ml was injected intracarpally, and 0.5 ml was injected intravenously.
Assay - Comments: The epitope was deduced by study of overlapping peptides. Infected goat serum reactivity with the epitope in the ELISA was detected between 12 weeks and 32 weeks postinfection.

1st immunogen - Name: Caprine arthritis encephalitis virus (Caprine arthritis-encephalitis virus)
Assay - Comments: The epitope was deduced by study of overlapping peptides. Sera from arthritic goats showed higher reactivity to the epitope than sera from infected asymptomatic goats.

Reference - Authors: Zhe Hu; Hao Chang; Xiaoyu Chu; Shuang Li; Meiyue Wang; Xiaojun Wang
Reference - Title: Identification and characterization of a common B-cell epitope on EIAV capsid proteins.
1st immunogen - Name: gag protein
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 5 doses of 100ug p26 antigen at two week intervals
Immunization - Comments: Mice were primed with 100ug of purified p26 in adjuvant and immunized 3 additional times with same antigen. A final booster immunization with purified p26 was given at 3 days before cell fusion. Mouse spleen cells were fused with mouse myeloma SP2/0 cells. Details of this procedure were provided in Hu et al. 2014 [PMID:25256618].
Assay - Comments: The epitope-specific mAb recognized EIAV-infected fetal donkey dermal cells by IFA.
Assay Antigen - Name: Equine infectious anemia virus (equine infectious anemia virus EIAV)

Reference - Authors: Jason Gorman; Rosemarie D Mason; Leonard Nettey; Nicole Cavett; Gwo-Yu Chuang; Dongjun Peng; Yaroslav Tsybovsky; Raffaello Verardi; Richard Nguyen; David Ambrozak; Kristin Biris; Celia C LaBranche; Akshaya Ramesh; Chaim A Schramm; Jing Zhou; Robert T Bailer; Thomas B Kepler; David C Montefiori; Lawrence Shapiro; Daniel C Douek; John R Mascola; Mario Roederer; Peter D Kwong
Reference - Title: Isolation and Structure of an Antibody that Fully Neutralizes Isolate SIVmac239 Reveals Functional Similarity of SIV and HIV Glycan Shields.
Epitope - Reference Name: Epitope of ITS90.03 Fab on SIV Env gp120
Epitope - Comments: The epitope residues were calculated from [PDB: 6TYB] as the antigen residues at 4Å atomic distance from the antibody.
1st immunogen - Name: Simian immunodeficiency virus - mac251
Immunization - Comments: A rhesus macaque (NHP 8-114) was SIV-infected by 6 weekly, preputial SIVmac251 exposures. Sera from the animal showed complete neutralization of the well-characterized neutralization-resistant SIVmac239 as well as of additional tier 2 and 3 SIV strains 46 weeks post-infection (p.i.). Memory B cells from NP 8-114 at 27 weeks p.i. were sorted for binding to SIVmac239 gp140 foldon trimer but negative for 1JO8-V1V2 SIVmac239. This led to isolation of monoclonal antibody ITS90.03.
Assay - Location of Assay Data in Refere: Figures 3, S2, Table S1 and PDB 6TYB
Assay - Comments: The epitope of ITS90.03 Fab on SIV gp120 was determined from the crystal structure of a fully glycosylated SIVmac239-gp120 core in complex with rhesus CD4(domains 1 and 2) and the ITS90.03 Fab.

Epitope - Reference Name: Epitope of ITS90.03 Fab on SIV Env gp120
Epitope - Comments: The epitope residues were calculated from [PDB: 6TYB] as the antigen residues at 4Å atomic distance from the antibody.
1st immunogen - Name: Simian immunodeficiency virus - mac251
Immunization - Comments: A rhesus macaque (NHP 8-114) was SIV-infected by 6 weekly, preputial SIVmac251 exposures. Reference - Authors: Xiaohua Ma; Min Gao; Xiangmin Zhang; Weiwei Ma; Fei Xue; Xue-Feng Wang; Xiaojun Wang
Reference - Title: Identification and characterization of linear epitopes of monoclonal antibodies against the capsid proteins of small ruminant lentiviruses.
1st immunogen - Name: gag protein [Visna-maedi virus]
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 3 doses of 100 µg at a 3 week interval
Assay - Comments: The epitope specific mAb bound the analogous peptide from MVV strain NM (genotype A2), SRLV genotypes A2, A4, A8, and B1, CAEV genotype B1, and ovine lentivirus genotype A1.  The mAb failed to bind a peptide from a SRLV strain with unidentified subtypes isolated from Ovis aries in Jordan carrying R198K/Q201T substitutions.
